  "prompt": "What are some side dishes for tortellini?",
  "response": "Tortellini is a versatile pasta that pairs well with a variety of side dishes. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Garlic Bread**: Garlic bread is a classic side that complements the flavors of tortellini, especially when served with a rich sauce.\n   \n2. **Salad**: A fresh salad can balance the richness of tortellini. Consider options like Caesar salad, arugula salad, or a simple mixed greens salad with a light vinaigrette.\n\n3. **Roasted Vegetables**: Roasted vegetables such as asparagus, zucchini, bell peppers, or broccoli can add a healthy and flavorful touch to your meal.\n\n4. **Sauteed Spinach**: A side of saut\u00e9ed spinach with garlic and olive oil adds a nutritious and tasty element to the dish.\n\n5. **Bruschetta**: Tomato bruschetta with basil and balsamic vinegar makes a refreshing side that pairs well with tortellini.\n\n6. **Caprese Salad**: Fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, and basil drizzled with olive oil and balsamic reduction offer a light and flavorful complement.\n\n7. **Antipasto Platter**: A selection of cured meats, cheeses, olives, and marinated vegetables can be a delightful and varied side.\n\n8. **Breadsticks**: Soft or crunchy breadsticks can be a nice accompaniment, particularly if you're serving tortellini with soup or a light sauce.\n\n9. **Stuffed Mushrooms**: Mushrooms stuffed with cheese, garlic, and herbs are an elegant and delicious side dish.\n\n10. **Grilled Eggplant**: Grilled eggplant with a touch of olive oil and herbs can provide a smoky, savory side to your tortellini.\n\nFeel free to mix and match based on your preferences and the specific type of tortellini dish you're serving!",
